<p>As with its minor brother, the major pentatonic scale is made up of 5 notes. It is a major scale, and its notes are derived from the full major scale. To arrive at the major pentatonic scale, we omit the 4th and 7th tones. The scale will still have its major flavor, since the triad notes of major scales (1st, 3rd, 5th) remain untouched.
<br><b><center>
1 W 2 W 3 W+H 5 W 6 W+H 8(1)
</center></b>
<br> 
