<h4> PRACTICING THE PENTATONIC SCALE </h4>
<ol>
<li>Get used to the boxed shape rooting on the low E string at first. If you get that down, move on to rooting it on the A string.</li>
<li>Don’t just pluck the notes in sequence, mix up the notes.</li>
<li>Skip around the notes of the scale, add lead guitar elements to make it even more interesting.</li>
<li>Try making up short riffs using the notes of the scale and the lead guitar techniques.</li>
</ol>